cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with partial order reduction, which is a technique used to tackle state-space explosion caused by concurrency. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a novel stateless POR algorithm that explores at most one execution per Mazurkiewicz trace. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses state-caching and explores ways to reduce the number of executions. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes a method to cope with non-terminating executions. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper defines unfolding semantics for an abstract execution model.
